responded: Here is the improved patch. It adds a check for excessive `nestingLevel` at the very start of `parseChoiceStyle`, just as is done in `parseMessage` and `parseArg`. This ensures that no matter how `parseChoiceStyle` is entered, recursion will be bounded and stack overflow prevented.

```diff
--- a/icu4c/source/common/messagepattern.cpp
+++ b/icu4c/source/common/messagepattern.cpp
@@ -701,6 +701,11 @@
 int32_t
 MessagePattern::parseChoiceStyle(int32_t index, int32_t nestingLevel,
                                  UParseError *parseError, UErrorCode &errorCode) {
+    if(nestingLevel > Part::MAX_VALUE) {
+        errorCode = U_INDEX_OUTOFBOUNDS_ERROR;
+        return 0;
+    }
+
     if(U_FAILURE(errorCode)) {
         return 0;
     }
